GENERAL INFORMATION
-------------------

(1) Title of the Dataset:

Replication Data for: Computational Insights into the Activation Mechanism of CXCR4: Implication for the Design of Small Molecule Agonists

DESCRIPTION
-----------

(1) Language:

English

(2) Abstract:

This repository contains inputs files, starting structures and developed specific parameters necessary to reproduce conformational free energy profiles, binding free energy calculations and the conventional all-atom Molecular Dynamics (MD) simulation of the HL82624-CXCR4 complex presented in the corresponding paper. All information regarding methodoly and settings employed can be found into computational methods section.

(3) Keywords:

CXCR4, activation mechanism, conformational free energy profiles, PDLD/S-LRA, conventional MD simulations.

(4) Data Type:

Simulation data

(5) Date of the dateset publication

2026-03-17 

METHODOLOGICAL INFORMATION
--------------------------

(1) Instrument- or Software-Specific Information Needed to Interpret the Data

        Molaris-XG package
        GROMACS2021 package

FILE OVERVIEW
-------------

(1) Folder Organization

Note: Input files are specified in the order in which they should be executed.

/All_Atom_MD_Simulation
	/Inputs
		File list:
			  - insert.mdp; ions.mdp; membed.dat [Insertion of the HL82624-CXCR4 complex into POPC membrane along with its solvation and charge neutralization]
			  - em.mdp [Initial minimization]
			  - heating_200ps.mdp [Heating to reach T = 300 K]
			  - equil_200ns.mdp [Equilibration MD simulation]
			  - prod_300ns.mdp [Production MD simulation]
			
	/Parameters
		File list:
			  - HL82624.mol2 [Specific parameters developed for HL82624]

	/Starting_Structures
		File list:
			  - HF82624_CXCR4_mem.gro [HL82624-CXCR4 complex embedded into POPC bilayer solveted with TIP3P waters]

/CG_profiles_calculations
	/Inputs
		 File list:
              - steep_mini.inp [Initial minimization of the refined model of a given CXCR4 endpoint state]
			  - tmd_simulation.inp [TMD simulation to generate intermediate conformations of a given CXCR4 activation process]
			  - add_mem.inp [Incorporation of implicit membrane and subsequent minimization]
			  - heating_equil.inp [Heating and equilibration MD simulation for a given intermediate conformation]
			  - CG_calculation.inp [Minimization after system trimming and Coarse-Grained conformational free energy calculation]
	/Starting_Structures
		File list:
			  - AMD3100_induced_CXCR4_active_state.pdb [Refined model for the AMD3100-induced CXCR4 active state]
			  - AMD3100_induced_CXCR4_inactive_state.pdb [Refined model for the AMD3100-induced CXCR4 inactive state]
			  - HL82624_induced_First_CXCR4_inactive_state.pdb [Refined model for the HL82624-induced CXCR4 inactive state obtained for the first frame of the production period of the conventional all-atom MD simulation of the HL82624-CXCR4 complex]
			  - HL82624_induced_Last_CXCR4_inactive_state.pdb [Refined model for the HL82624-induced CXCR4 inactive state obtained for the last frame of the production period of the conventional all-atom MD simulation of the HL82624-CXCR4 complex]
			  - IT1t_induced_CXCR4_inactive_state.pdb [Refined model for the IT1t-induced CXCR4 inactive state]
			  - SDF1alpha_induced_CXCR4_active_state.pdb [Refined model for the SDF1alpha-induced CXCR4 active state]
			  - SDV1a_induced_CXCR4_active_state.pdb [Refined model for the SDV1a-induced CXCR4 active state]
			  - W94_E288_rotamer_IT1t_induced_CXCR4_inactive_state.pdb [Refined model for the IT1t-induced CXCR4 inactive state with W94 adjusted to its active-state conformation]
			  - W94_rotamer_IT1t_induced_CXCR4_inactive_state.pdb [Refined model for the IT1t-induced CXCR4 inactive state with W94 and E288 adjusted to their active-state conformations]

/PDLD_S_LRA_Simulations
	/Inputs
		File list:
			  - add_mem_PDLD.inp [Incorporation of implicit membrane and subsequent minimization]
			  - heating_equil.inp [Heating and equilibration MD simulation for a given complex of HF51116 or its fragments with CXCR4]
			  - Binding_calculation.inp [PDLD/S-LRA simulation to calculate the binding free energy of a given complex of HF51116 or its fragments with CXCR4]
	/Parameters
		File list:
			  - F01.mol2 [Specific parameters developed for F01 fragment of HF51116]
			  - F02.mol2 [Specific parameters developed for F02 fragment of HF51116]
			  - HF51116.mol2 []Specific parameters developed for HF51116]
	/Starting_Structures
		File list:
			  - F01_CXCR4.pdb [Refined model for the F01-bound CXCR4 inactive state]
			  - F02_CXCR4.pdb [Refined model for the F02-bound CXCR4 inactive state]
			  - HF51116_CXCR4.pdb [Refined model for the HF51116-bound CXCR4 inactive state]
